{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17584002","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17584002"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:35:08+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:35:08+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14214"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"14214","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/14214"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.01,0.02,0.02,0.02,0.93]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6900"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96070"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6900","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6900"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14214"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78802"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"4"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"66"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"98"},{"type":"tags","id":"191"},{"type":"tags","id":"1804"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"4991"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5351"},{"type":"tags","id":"8126"},{"type":"tags","id":"11622"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12734"},{"type":"tags","id":"12920"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"15756"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32920"},{"type":"contributions","id":"40256"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96070","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/96070"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 45-year-old Aboriginal man presents to a rural General Practice clinic with poorly controlled type 2 diabetes. He has a history of hypertension and obesity. He does not take any regular medications. The patient expresses frustration with previous healthcare experiences and difficulty in understanding his condition. He mentions feeling uncomfortable discussing his health concerns with non-Indigenous healthcare providers.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOn examination, he appears well. His pulse rate is 78/min, blood pressure 145/90 mmHg, respiratory rate 16/min, SpO2 98% on room air, and temperature 36.7\u00b0C. His BMI is 32 kg/m2. His HbA1c is 9.5% (80 mmol/mol).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate next step to improve this patient\u0027s engagement with healthcare and management of his chronic conditions?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Recommend a low-carbohydrate diet and daily exercise","Provide written educational materials about diabetes","Refer to an endocrinologist","Prescribe metformin and arrange follow-up in one month","Involve an Aboriginal Health Worker in the patient\u0027s care"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EIn this scenario, involving an \u003Cstrong\u003EAboriginal Health Worker\u003C/strong\u003E in the patient\u0027s care is the most appropriate next step to improve his engagement with healthcare and management of chronic conditions. Aboriginal Health Workers play a crucial role in providing culturally appropriate healthcare and bridging the gap between Indigenous communities and health services.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReferring to an endocrinologist\u003C/strong\u003E may be beneficial for managing complex diabetes cases, but it does not address the patient\u0027s expressed discomfort with non-Indigenous healthcare providers and may not improve his engagement with healthcare.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrescribing metformin and arranging follow-up\u003C/strong\u003E is an important aspect of diabetes management, but it does not address the underlying issues of cultural barriers and the patient\u0027s frustration with previous healthcare experiences.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProviding written educational materials\u003C/strong\u003E about diabetes may be helpful, but it does not address the patient\u0027s difficulty in understanding his condition and the need for culturally appropriate communication.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERecommending a low-carbohydrate diet and daily exercise\u003C/strong\u003E is important for diabetes management, but it does not address the patient\u0027s engagement issues and the need for culturally sensitive care.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EAboriginal Health Workers can provide culturally appropriate health education, assist with communication between the patient and healthcare providers, and help develop management plans that are culturally sensitive and acceptable to the patient. They can also provide support in navigating the healthcare system and addressing social determinants of health that may impact the patient\u0027s ability to manage his chronic conditions effectively.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBy involving an Aboriginal Health Worker, the healthcare team can improve the patient\u0027s understanding of his condition, enhance his engagement with healthcare services, and develop a more holistic and culturally appropriate approach to managing his diabetes and other chronic conditions. This collaboration between Aboriginal Health Workers and other healthcare professionals is essential for improving health outcomes in Indigenous populations.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Aboriginal Health Workers play a crucial role in providing culturally appropriate healthcare and bridging the gap between Indigenous communities and health services.","Aboriginal Health Workers contribute to health promotion, disease prevention, and management of chronic conditions in Indigenous communities.","Collaboration between Aboriginal Health Workers and other healthcare professionals is essential for improving health outcomes in Indigenous populations."],"references":["Jeyakumar R, Patel B, Coombes J, Madden T, Joshi R. \u201cWe\u0027re on the ground, we know what needs to be done\u201d: Exploring the role of Aboriginal Health Workers in primary health care. Frontiers in Public Health. 2023 Jan 19;10:1010301."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78802"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14214"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78802","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/78802"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-30T21:44:26+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-04-01T14:16:51+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6900"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"96070"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"4","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6c","name":"Endocrinology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"66","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/66"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Management","synonyms":null,"description":null,"positi